title: For Sale:  Pre-modded, one of a kind Franken-Mosin super sniper
location: Cleveland - Akron - Youngstown, Ohio, United States
postcontent:
This is one of my most prized firearms. I hate to part with it, but it's served me well and I need cash for my 3Gun addiction or possibly a boat motor/trailer.

First off, it's a 1943 Tula ex sniper with one of the cleanest barrels ive ever seen. I'd give it an 8/10 plenty of rifling and it shines. You can see inside the reciever where the original p/u scope was removed. It is not matching numbers (who cares). It is an absolute accuracy machine. At 100 yards you will get 1 inch groups. At 50 yards you will chew out the damn bullseye. I have kept the barrel clean meticulously. 

Now let's talk upgrades. 

-eBay butt pad
- trigger slack spring (poor mans 2 stage trigger)
-bent bolt handle
- Texas precision products muzzle brake (thing rocks)
- sling lugs drilled into the stock for bipod and monopod (secured with JB weld. Solid as a rock)
- genuine Harris side to side swivel bipod 9-13" 
-accu-shot monopod (that's right. A fucking monopod)
-Jmeck barrel wrap tall scope mount (let's you see through the iron sights)
- eBay cheek pad.
-eBay pistol grip is also drilled into the stock and JB welded

Currently mounted is a Primary Arms 4-14x Mil-Mil FFP mil dot scope. A true first focal plane scope which is revered throughout the shooting world as outrageous bang for your buck. Is mounted with some nice beefy hi quality rings and has butler creek flip caps.

The scope is optional and is a $300 set up on its own.

I would say conservative estimate of the rifle without the scope is $600. I spent 2 years, blood sweat and tears on it and that is a great price.

I took this bad boy to a distance shoot 2 weeks ago and was ringing stee targets from 200-700 yards with ease. That's how good the scope is. I was even ringing the hostage flapper at 240 yds no problem. Let's face it, this is as close as you're gonna get to a legit distance rifle without dropping over $1000 and it shoots 25¢ Ammo. I'm selling because I need gear for 3gun and ammo and it is sucking up all my damn money.

Serious offers please. Will consider ammo(.223, 9mm, 12g) other stuff, interesting firearms, steel targets, trolling motors, boat trailers, maybe a sweet compound bow, tree stand trail cams. 

I got more pics just ask and I get around I can travel for the right deal. I got some ammo for it too. Russian silver tip.  I'm located in Middlefield text or call 330-607-3194
